cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or the VETO benchmark, please cite the paper below."
title: "The Wrong Kind of Right: Quantifying and Localizing Misfired Alignment in LLMs"
abstract: >-
  Alignment aims to ensure that large language models (LLMs) behave safely and
  reliably, including by avoiding unsafe inferences. However, such
  safety-oriented behaviors can misfire: models may reject warranted conclusions
  even when they are explicitly supported by context. We call this failure mode
  misfired alignment. We introduce VETO, a benchmark of 2,032 BBQ-derived
  contrastive pairs, and the Misfired Alignment Rate (MAR) metric, benchmark 25
  LLMs, and localize a late-layer suppression mechanism through mechanistic
  analysis.
type: software
